{"body":"## Summary

MCP integration tests (`mcp-serve.integration.test.ts`, `mcp-e2e.integration.test.ts`) are now failing **consistently** in CI, not just intermittently. This was observed on both the #490 branch and main during the same timeframe.

## Failing Tests (8 total)

- `mcp-e2e.integration.test.ts` > Graceful shutdown > AC-8: should disconnect SSE client cleanly on SIGTERM
- `mcp-serve.integration.test.ts` > AC-16: graceful shutdown > should exit cleanly on SIGTERM for SSE server
- `mcp-serve.integration.test.ts` > AC-16: graceful shutdown > should exit cleanly on SIGINT for SSE server
- `mcp-serve.integration.test.ts` > AC-11: MCP client detection > should detect MCP client config paths for current platform
- `mcp-serve.integration.test.ts` > AC-11: MCP client detection > should generate valid sequant MCP config entry
- `mcp-serve.integration.test.ts` > AC-11: MCP client detection > should add sequant config to an existing MCP config file
- `mcp-serve.integration.test.ts` > AC-11: MCP client detection > should create config file and parent directories if they don't exist
- `mcp-serve.integration.test.ts` > error scenarios > should handle port already in use for SSE transport

## Root Cause

The `afterEach` hook at `mcp-serve.integration.test.ts:114` times out at 60s (vitest default `hookTimeout`). It kills process groups via `SIGKILL` and waits for exit, but the promise never resolves — likely because:

1. The spawned process group has already exited by the time the listener is registered (race condition between `proc.exitCode` check and `proc.on("exit", ...)`)
2. OR GitHub Actions runner changes affected process group signal delivery

## History

- Originally fixed in 2026-03-23 with `detached: true` + process group signaling
- Was documented as "passes consistently in GitHub Actions CI" but that is no longer true
- Observed failing consistently on main as of 2026-04-06 (run IDs: 24022361055, 24022099503)

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] `afterEach` cleanup handles the race condition where process exits before listener is registered
- [ ] Add explicit timeout to the exit promise (e.g., 5s) with forced resolution to prevent 60s hangs
- [ ] All 8 tests pass consistently in CI (run 3x to verify)
- [ ] Update `project_ci_known_failures.md` memory to reflect current status

## Suggested Fix

```typescript
afterEach(async () => {
  const exitPromises = spawnedProcesses.map(
    (proc) =>
      new Promise<void>((resolve) => {
        if (proc.exitCode !== null || proc.killed) {
          resolve();
          return;
        }
        const timeout = setTimeout(() => resolve(), 5000);
        proc.on("exit", () => {
          clearTimeout(timeout);
          resolve();
        });
        killProcessGroup(proc, "SIGKILL");
      }),
  );
  await Promise.all(exitPromises);
  spawnedProcesses.length = 0;
});
